@node config "CK.gonfig"
@{b}Config:
@{ub}
CK reads it's configuration from the CK.config file. If the file is missing
or something is wrong with it then CK won't start. So be carefull with it.

@{b}Configuration options:
@{ub}
General format for option is '#:COMMAND:PARAM  (;COMMENT)

@{b}Command list:
@{ub}
NAME        COMMAND     PARAM       DESC
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
SOUNDS      S           Y - ON      This option turns game sounds on or off.
                        N - OFF     It is usefull if you cannot free enought 
                                    chip mem to run this game on 512KB chip 
                                    machines, or want to play your own 
                                    modules during the game.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
TRACKING    T           Y - ON      This option shows your exact location     
                        N - OFF     on game maps with red spot.
                                    Turning this option off will make game
                                    very challenging (and unplayable).
---------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
TOWN DELAY  M           0 - 9       This option sets the speed of 
                        0 - fast    town/dungeon movemens. Value 2 is good
                        9 - slow    for both A500 and 40MHZ/030 machines.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
WILDERNESS  W           0 - 9       This option sets the speed of wilderness
DELAY                   0 - fast    movement. Value 0 is good for 40MHZ/030
                        9 - slow    and slower machines.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
@endnode

